modelVersions.name: v1.0
modelVersions.description:
The clothing in this version leans towards cheongsam and has good generalization, making it suitable for many large models. What's even more surprising is that the composition and atmosphere of the image differ depending on the different base models. You can try combining it with various cyber elements, as well as keywords related to technology-related vehicles and props for a more immersive experience.

For clothing color, you can also try pairing two colors together, such as blue/pink, black/red, blue/white, or red/green, which all make for great combinations.

As for movements, currently standing and sitting poses are more easily triggered, but it depends on whether the animation is compatible and generalized enough with the model.

The example images are all produced directly from the modelï¼š

AWportrait https://civitai.com/models/61170/awportrait,

lyriel https://civitai.com/models/22922/lyriel

Guofeng3 https://civitai.com/models/10415/3-guofeng3

majicMIX reverie https://civitai.com/models/65055/majicmix-reverie

I hope that everyone will try it out and welcome any feedback or suggestion!

items.name: Pom Pom (Human Ver.) LoRA
items.description:
Pom Pom (Female Human Version) LoRA

I saw a picture on pixiv of this and decided to make a model off of it lmao.

LoRA request queue on my discord: https://discord.gg/DAfjhRfyEM

This model was trained using 24 images of Pom Pom's human version. I used bucketing in v2 and got a way more consistent result, but at the same time it got pretty lewd, so I'll mark it as mature xD

Recommended weight is 0.8 to 1.

Trigger word is pompom, if you don't prompt anything else you will get some very lewd bodystockings, so you might want to prompt certain things out if you want something sfw.

Example images were generated using jafaMix with 30 steps, and hires fix to 1.5x size with 0.4 denoising strength.

Note: This was made exclusively on anime images and on an anime checkpoint. Feel free to post images on realistic, semirealistic etc. checkpoints, but do not rate it on that! This was made to be used on anime checkpoints so keep reviews for that!

items.name: Ashley - Hentai University
items.description:
This is a LoRA for the character Ashley, from Hentai University a game by Noodle Jacuzzi.

Ashley's art is from the artist Silver Radish, the set -

Doeroi Gal ga Arawareta!!

I've been working my way through making these for all the characters currently in the game, and sharing them in the Discord for HU, but figured I should also put them up here.

In general, I'm working from pretty limited image sets, so expect the results to be a bit wonky at times. These (and the rest of the gym girls) especially only have about 15 images to work from each, and they're not ideal images. It still works, but it takes more finagling that some of the other characters for sure.

I recommend a weight of around 0.5, possibly lower depending if you're combining the character LoRA with other styles/costumes/etc. along with tagging some defining characteristics of the character you're generating. Higher than that can really push the artist's original style, and may cause you issues.

All characters I train have a "character tag" added into the set to help generate them fairly reliably.

Recommended LoRA Weight - 0.5 for fairly flexible, higher if you want more of the original artist's style, lower if it doesn't play nice with other loras.

Character tag - HUAshley
Recommended tags - black hair, blue hair, gradient hair, long hair, brown eyes, large breasts, glasses, ponytail,

I may have forgotten to check and tag eye color when doing my testing, but hey. If you want it to be "set accurate" be sure to tag.

I've got quite a backlog of these made up already, so I'll be uploading them on and off.

Check my other uploads as I put them out for more HU characters, and if you want any specific character put up soon, let me know.

items.name: Lilac
items.description:
What is Lilac?

Lilac is a cartoonish anime style model primarily designed in creating images for children's books, graphic novels, comics, kids' illustrations and promotional arts. It has its own unique aesthetics compared to my other model Plum.Â  I personally use this model for my works, which is well suited on one of my styles. Regarding text prompts, just be versatile and let your imagination flow.Â  And, just like most models it also has few issues with the hands, which can be easily mitigated with this model's inpainting (download separately) or some embeddings. (I still have other models, for some specific arts, yet to be released. Your support will go a long way, and a cup of coffee will keep me awake for many nights. Thank you in advance!)

This version of Lilac does not include a VAE because the goal is for art versatility, wherein, you can use any VAE you like to produce unique aesthetics. Below are the recommended VAEs that you can use with this model to tweak a unique output.

Popular Variable Auto Encoder (VAE)

kl-f8-anime2 VAE (for anime)

anything VAE aka orangemix VAE (for anime)

blessed VAE (for anime)

vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned (for realism)

Sample images above were created with simple text prompts around default settings. More detailed prompts will produce much better results. As for text prompts, just let your imagination flow. One thing to take note, adding keywords like realistic, realism, photorealism, photorealistic, hyperrealism, hyper realistic etc. will make the image more real, and not including any word with real on them will make it look cartoonish or anime-ish.

Settings:

Sampling Method: Euler (realistic) or Euler A (anime)

Sampling Steps: 20 to 30

Resolution: 512x512, 512x768, 768x512

CFG Scale: 4 to 7

Popular Embeddings Used

Easy Negative

Deep Negative

Bad artist Negative embedding

veryBadImageNegative

bad_prompt Negative Embedding

negative_hand Negative Embedding

EnvyBetterHands LoCon

Detail Tweaker LoRA

SXZ Vivid Darkness

Theovercomer8's Contrast Fix

Limitations:

Do use this model within the boundaries of legalities; do not use it to harm people and entities, or any illegal matters. Using this model means that you alone are responsible for any forms of consequences good or bad, and the author has no liabilities. We all know that AI models can produce both safe and unsafe images for work, so be very responsible.Â  For all other matters do read the CreativeML-OpenRail-M license Other than that, enjoy using this model and I hope this will help you in your endeavours as an artist.

Support:

First of all, thank you for patronizing this model; it means my efforts didn't go to waste. My goal is to produce more free tools not just for myself and my work, but for others too. Your generosity will go more than a mile. Also, as an artist, writer, programmer, and overall freelancer, I accept commission job. Thank you so much for your support!

After 121 models, 494 hours of processing, 2800 likes and 20K downloads, I want to sincerely thank the 7 people in total who supported me to make those models.

The model removed by Civitai will be reposted with prude CIVITAI standart showcase.

Bicentennial Man is a 1999 American science fiction comedy-drama film starring Robin Williams, Sam Neill, Embeth Davidtz (in a dual role), Wendy Crewson, and Oliver Platt. Based on the 1992 novel The Positronic Man by Isaac Asimov and Robert Silverberg (which is itself based on Asimov's original 1976 novelette "The Bicentennial Man"), the plot explores issues of humanity, slavery, prejudice, maturity, intellectual freedom, conformity, sex, love, mortality, and eternal life. The film, a co-production between Touchstone Pictures and Columbia Pictures, was directed by Chris Columbus. The title comes from the main character existing to the age of two hundred years.

Galatea is a female NDR-series positronic robot created by NorthAm Robotics. She acts as an assistant to roboticist Rupert Burns and has a personality chip that allows her to express herself as a cheerful, extroverted person who enjoys singing and dancing. Replacing the chip with a different one can radically alter her behavior, however.

This character was created specifically for the film and is not present in the original story.

This model is trained with SFW sources only. If you get NSFW content, you did it in purpose, didn't you?

Please provide constructive criticism.

You can support me here to be able to render better models (https://ko-fi.com/djo226). Supporters can request model.

items.name: Hyper Pecs
items.description:
ABOUT

Hyper Pecs aim to give muscle male character with bigger pecs or make the pecs muscle look more heavy and strong and perhaps soft too.

The Pecs size can be control on how strong the lora and the prompt you put into it. The stronger the strength you add to the prompt, the bigger it will get like <lora:Hyper Pecs v2:0.5> (gigantic pecs:1.2) . The lora strength at 0.5 should be strong enough, you just need to add the strength on the prompt.

Version 2.0

This version 2 I decide to make it as hybrid. I notice there are like 3 category when comes to style, realistic, anime and furry and each style tags differently. Regardless, Hyper Pecs initially only works for Furry model but now it should be possible to be used for other style model. If it still not able to generate with this lora, that model doesn't have the model I use to train this lora.

Problems

I don't know how to prompt for realistic so I always end up with weird result. I notice these realistic human model, when the pecs become too big, it will generate skin stretch marks, other than that would be weird nipple. Anime is not big deal, seems to work just fine which same goes with furry model.

=Training=

The Lora was trained with mix of Boyfusion, Unstable Homerotic Diffusion and fluffyrock-lion-low-lr-e27. All of them are Trained model and I believe they're been uses alot in other model merge. items.name: C++AravaggioV0.9 - an Answer to both Dall-E and Kandinsky 2.1
items.description:
EDIT: after the negative feedback i should make clear that the model is not completely a SD 1.5 and because of that it needs a different approach on generating images, the negative embedding i'm linking here should facilitate the use of negative prompt which is quite hard to get right on this model.

The model is tested on Automatic1111.

If you're having troubles generating images - if they look that bad - it's possibly a problem of your graphics card (turn the random number generator to CPU).

Another trick is that the ENSD works better set to 99999 rather than 31337, check it out for yourself.

If you can't in any way reproduce the images, even with the embeddings, try copying the info from the example images, it should help.

https://civitai.com/models/93766/embeddings-pack-for-caravaggio-reupload-with-images

This model is not perfect and I'm very well aware of that, this was the first step of my current model which I'd rather not publish yet, anyway it still has plenty of power.

(VAE baked in, the model comes with some textual inversions, 768x768 resolution)

The procedure in making this model was first of all some merges, then i finetuned a 1.5 basic model with some of my black and white drawings/sketches (im not that much of an artist but it worked very good because it took the style in a nice way, making each humanoid output quite different from both anime and semirealistic models.

After i merged even the model finetuned on my drawings on this, then i took the final model and dissected it with the kohya extract diffusers tool... why? Because there are better text encoders around than the base one of Stable Diffusion! And in fact i scraped off Huggingface and tested each one to find the best compatibility. Now this model seems to understand well structured english, you can easily ask ChatGPT for a story and try it on this model, or copy your Midjourney prompts here... it works fine, but it ain't Midjourney, obviously.

This model was trained using the collab/guide by holostrawberry [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free - colabs | Stable Diffusion Other | Civitai

The generation was selected based on testing in AOM3. I recommend experimenting with the weights when using other checkpoints.

About the artist:

Hanabushi makes highly stylized art and is most well known for making the art of the following music video:

Check out the artist here:

Twitter: ã¯ãªã¶ã—ğŸš€KUNG-FU-PIGGY (@hanabushi_) / Twitter

Instagram: ã¯ãªãµã‚™ã—âœ¨KUNG-FU-PIGGYğŸ’«ğŸš€ (@hanabushi_) on Instagram

Weights & Prompts

AOM3 volatile:

I recommend using weights of 0.8-1.0, adjusted to taste. Check the XYZ plots for a detailed breakdown. This version was specifically trained on AOM3 and probably won't work nearly as well on any other checkpoint.

It can really struggle with anatomy, hands and teeth (especially when depicting full bodies) so I recommend using more than just a few seeds per prompt. As you can see in the examples the range between the good and the "bad" is pretty big.

Unlike v1.0 this version is a lot better at depicting prompted backgrounds and landscapes in the right style. Setting the weight to .9 tends to be enough to reduce the random semi japanese symbols.

v1.0:

For me it worked with a weight of 1.0. As usual I have included XYZ plots for reference.

Some useful prompts:

color contrast, limited palette, flat color

As a small sidenote, it looks like stable diffusion picks up on the "piggy" in the prompt and will occassionally put pigs into landscapes.

items.name: Emma Wortelboer
items.description:
Want to buy me coffee? (Buy a cup)

Biography

Emma Wortelboer, a vibrant and charismatic television presenter and personality hailing from the Netherlands, has captured the hearts of audiences with her infectious energy and quirky charm. Born on October 26, 1996, Emma rose to fame through her appearances on popular Dutch television shows, where her unapologetically genuine and unpredictable nature made her an instant favorite. Her captivating presence and quick wit have made her a sought-after host for various events, including the Eurovision Song Contest in 2019. With her signature flamboyant style and boundless enthusiasm, Emma Wortelboer continues to leave an indelible mark on the entertainment industry, making her a beloved figure both on and off screen.

items.name: Furisode Fur Collar
items.description:
A lora for generating Japanese furisode with the fur collar/scarf. I couldn't for the life of me find the Japanese name for it, but you see it worn during special events like New Years or the coming-of-age ceremony.

It's pretty simple to use, the trigger is "furifur kimono". The general result is a white collar, but it sometimes does black or colorful ones too.

Post your pictures if you make some good ones! I'd love to see.

items.name: Comically Large Spoon | Concept LoRA
items.description:
Comically Large Spoon | Concept LoRA

"Only 1 spoon." ~ famous last words.

Weight can go from 0.7 up to 1. I recommend 1. ControlNet will streamline full body shots much easier, or more complex poses. Works with almost every Style, every Character and Photorealistic Models (kinda).

Trigger Word:

ComicallyLargeSpoon

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Download LoRA

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA and use the triggerword

  • Make sure to change the weight if needed (by default it's :1)

  • Have Fun!
